Approach:-
Use two pointers to traverse both strings simultaneously.
- Start from index 0 of both strings.
- Take one character from word1, then one from word2, and add them to the answer.
- Continue until one string is completely traversed.
- If any string has remaining characters, append them at the end.
- Convert the list into a string and return.

Code:-
class Solution(object):
    def mergeAlternately(self, word1, word2):
        i = 0
        j = 0
        ans = []
        while(i<len(word1) and j<len(word2)):
            ans.append(word1[i])
            ans.append(word2[j])
            i+=1
            j+=1

        while(i<len(word1)):
            ans.append(word1[i])
            i+=1
        
        while(j<len(word2)):
            ans.append(word2[j])
            j+=1

        return "".join(ans)

Time Complexity: O(n + m)
Space Complexity: O(n + m)
